race.comment: Tricky race with a few of these that take turns winning. THINK TANK (1) was disappointing last start but he clearly has ability, as seen in his win two starts back. He needs the Goldilocks scenario but if things go his way and he gets the right from the draw, he can win. Garret Lynch has a strong hand in the race and AMBITIOUS CREEK (7) might be the best of his chances. He is a last-start winner at Morphettville. He is rock-hard fit and can roll along somewhere near the speed. He will look the winner at some point. CHARTIN (8) is another on-pacer that will make his own luck. He doesn't win out of turn but he must be included, particularly on a track that can favour on-pacers. GRINZINGER JOY (4) has been at her best here at Balaklava so must be a place chance, while MR TRAFFICANTI (3) looks ready to peak and should be given some thought for exotics.
